list.abstract: out，英语单词，可以用作副词、动词、形容词、名词、介词，翻译为在外部、驱逐、外面的、不流行、（从…里）出来等意思。
示例当希望方法返回多个值时，声明 out方法很有用。使用 out参数的方法仍然可以将变量用作返回类型（请参见 return），但它还可以将一个或多个对象作为 out参数返回给调用方法。此示例使用 out在一个方法调用中返回三个变量。请注意，第三个参数所赋的值为 Null。这样便允许方法有选择地返回值。

yingyinNormal.en: Uh, he got out Lotso. Got out?
yingyinNormal.zh: 呃，他逃出来了，抱抱熊。逃出来了?

yingyinNormal.en: The hair comes out and the gloves come off.
yingyinNormal.zh: 头发冒了出来，手套滑落下来 (全都发泄出来了)。

yingyinNormal.en: So, can I come into the out now?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那么，放我出来吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Has your mucus plug popped out?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的宫颈粘液栓排出来了吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Excellent! Can I come into the out now?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好极了！放我出来吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Truck, wiggle out, jump, run.
yingyinNormal.zh: 上卡车，扭出来，跳下去，快跑。

yingyinNormal.en: Dad. Dad. I got out. I'm okay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 爸爸，爸爸，我出来了，我没事。

yingyinNormal.en: I'd rather have a cigarette. Spit it out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我更想抽根烟。吐出来吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on, lay it out. I'm a good listener.
yingyinNormal.zh: 快点儿，说出来，我洗耳恭听。

yingyinNormal.en: Help them. Help them. Get them out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 快去，救他们，快去救他们，把他们救出来。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on out. Let's see what you put together.
yingyinNormal.zh: 出来吧，让我看看你穿上后的效果。

yingyinNormal.en: Why are you out here? My computer's been hacked.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们出来做什么？我的电脑被黑了。

yingyinNormal.en: Let's dig it out. It's a metal coin. Treasure. Hooray.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们把它挖出来。这是一枚硬币。是宝藏！好棒！

yingyinNormal.en: It's Finn Polmar coming out of your wife's apartment building.
yingyinNormal.zh: 芬恩·波尔马，正从你妻子的公寓大楼走出来。

yingyinNormal.en: Knock door-to-door, if necessary. Clear these bastards out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 必要的话，挨家挨户的查，把这些混蛋都揪出来。

yingyinNormal.en: The doors opened, and out you came. Astronaut Jack Harper.
yingyinNormal.zh: 舱门一打开，你们就走了出来。宇航员杰克哈珀。

yingyinNormal.en: I got out to pee a couple times. Then I didn't get out to pee a couple times.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我中间出来撒过几次尿，也有几次没出来就在里面尿了。

yingyinNormal.en: It's not right to steal, but we don't kill people for it. Come out. Come out this instant.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你偷东西是不对的，但是我们也不会为此杀你，出来，立刻给我出来。

yingyinNormal.en: You got your whole life ahead of you! We'll help you, kid! Get him out! Get him out of there!
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在拿你的生命冒险! 我们会帮你的,孩子! 把他弄出来! 把他弄出来!

yingyinNormal.en: Penelope. Farkle. It came out. It just came out. It came out. It just came out. Penelope?
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩内洛普。弗科。是我口不择言，嘴快，一不小心说出来了。佩内洛普？

examination_example.sentence: Optimists point <highlight>out</highlight> that technological upheaval has benefited workers in the past.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 乐观主义者指出，技术变革在过去曾给工人带来益处。

examination_example.sentence: Koehn pointed <highlight>out</highlight> that this new era of corporate vocabulary is very "team" - oriented — and not by coincidence.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 科恩指出，这个企业词汇的新时代具有很强的“团队”导向，这并非巧合。

examination_example.sentence: Mark Baldassare of the Public Policy Institute of California points <highlight>out</highlight> that much of the state's budget is patrolled by unions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 加州公共政策研究所的Mark Baldassare指出，该州的大部分预算都是受工会监督的。

sense_info_list.en: away from the inside of a place or thing

examination_example.sentence: Head toward these breaks to find a way <highlight>out</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 朝这些岔路口走，寻找出路。

examination_example.sentence: The bargain is very pure: Employee puts in hours of physical or mental labor and employee draws <highlight>out</highlight> life-sustaining moola.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种交易非常纯粹：雇员投入数小时的体力或脑力劳动，然后抽出维持生活的毛利。

examination_example.sentence: Think of those fleeting moments when you look <highlight>out</highlight> of an aeroplane window and realise that you are flying, higher than a bird.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当你望向窗外，想到那些飞逝的瞬间，发觉自己飞得比鸟儿还高。

examination_example.sentence: "We humans seem to be fascinated by robots, and it turns <highlight>out</highlight> other animals are too," says Wiles.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “我们人类似乎对机器人很着迷，事实证明，其他动物也一样。”怀尔斯说。

examination_example.sentence: The move turned <highlight>out</highlight> to be foresighted.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实证明，此举是有先见之明的。

examination_example.sentence: Of even greater concern is the fact that obesity turns <highlight>out</highlight> to be very difficult to define.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 更令人担忧的是，事实证明肥胖是很难定义的。

sense_info_list.en: used to show that somebody or something is not or no longer in a particular state or condition

examination_example.sentence: Global climate change may get <highlight>out</highlight> of control.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 全球气候变化可能脱离控制。

examination_example.sentence: AI Shall Be Killers Once <highlight>Out</highlight> of Control
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人工智能一旦失控即为杀手

examination_example.sentence: Only then will they be useful servants and not Frankenstein's <highlight>out</highlight>-of-control monster.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 只有这样，他们才会成为有用的仆人，而非不受弗兰肯斯坦控制的怪物。

examination_example.sentence: California is leading the way, as it does on so many climate efforts, in figuring <highlight>out</highlight> the details.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 加州加利福尼亚正在引领人们弄清这些细节问题，就像它在许多气候问题上所做的努力一样。

examination_example.sentence: Taking a gap year to figure things <highlight>out</highlight> initially can help prevent stress and save money later on.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 休学一年，一开始就把事情弄明白，可以帮助防止压力，并在以后节省资金。

examination_example.sentence: Figuring <highlight>out</highlight> a way to accelerate that transition would make sense for them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 找出办法加速这种转变对他们来说是有意义的。

sense_info_list.en: to many people

examination_example.sentence: send <highlight>out</highlight> warning messages to their fellows
examination_example.sentence_trans: 向他们的同伴发出警告信息

examination_example.sentence: I can't afford to pay my monthly mortgage payments on my own, so I have to rent rooms <highlight>out</highlight> to people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我自己一个人付不起每月的房贷，所以不得不把房间租给别人。

examination_example.sentence: G.I. is just a military abbreviation meaning Government Issue, and it was on all of the articles handed <highlight>out</highlight> to soldiers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: G.I.只是一个军事缩写，表示“政府发给”，分发给士兵的所有物品上都印有这个符号。

sense_info_list.en: used to show where something comes from

examination_example.sentence: Those societies came <highlight>out</highlight> of the war with levels of enrollment that had been roughly constant at 3-5% of the relevant age groups.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 战争结束后，这些社会的入学率基本保持在相关年龄组的3-5%。

examination_example.sentence: Tronick himself is concerned that the worries about kids' use of screens are born <highlight>out</highlight> of an "oppressive ideology".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 特罗尼克自己也担心，对孩子使用屏幕的担忧源于一种“压迫性意识形态”。

examination_example.sentence: This movement, driven by powerful and diverse motivations, built a nation <highlight>out</highlight> of a wilderness.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在强大而多样的动机的驱使下，这场运动在一片荒野上催生了一个国家。

sense_info_list.en: at or to an end
sense_info_list.zh: 结束; 到底; 完全

examination_example.sentence: Those are all valid, but you need to take time to hear <highlight>out</highlight> your coworkers, too.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些都有道理，但你也需要花时间听完同事们的意见。

examination_example.sentence: Then his marriage failed, his career burned <highlight>out</highlight> and his drinking became serious.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 后来，他的婚姻破裂了，事业殆尽了，酗酒变得更严重了。

examination_example.sentence: The G.I. was the guy who stuck it <highlight>out</highlight> and drove back the Nazi reign of murder.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国大兵是坚持到底，推翻纳粹血腥统治的人。

examination_example.sentence: Scientists are increasingly seeking <highlight>out</highlight> visual artists to help them communicate their work to new audiences.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 科学家们越来越多地寻找视觉艺术家来帮助他们将自己的作品传达给新的观众。

examination_example.sentence: It was the purpose and responsibility of great minds to go forth and seek <highlight>out</highlight> the truth.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 伟大人物的目的和责任是前进并寻求真理。

examination_example.sentence: "Many young people assume a great deal of personal responsibility for educating themselves and actively seeking <highlight>out</highlight> opposing viewpoints," the survey concluded.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 调查总结道：“许多年轻人在自我教育方面承担了巨大的个人责任，并积极寻找反对意见。”

sense_info_list.en: no longer involved in a situation, competition, or activity

examination_example.sentence: This means prohibiting companies from using "unnecessary steps such as forcing them to click through multiple screens or listen to reasons why they shouldn't opt <highlight>out</highlight>."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这意味着禁止公司使用“不必要的做法，比如强迫消费者多次点击屏幕或听信那些他们不应该选择退出的原因”。

examination_example.sentence: The family's increasing poverty forced Dickens <highlight>out</highlight> of school at age 12 to work in Warren's Blacking Warehouse.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 家庭的日益贫困迫使狄更斯在12岁时辍学，在沃伦的鞋油仓库工作。

examination_example.sentence: The Times shouldn't waste time getting <highlight>out</highlight> of the print business, but only if they go about doing it the right way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 《纽约时报》不应该浪费时间退出印刷业务，除非他们采取正确的方式退出。

sense_info_list.en: used to make the meaning of a word stronger

examination_example.sentence: That means prioritizing <highlight>out</highlight> activities so that we spend most time on the things we really want to do.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这意味着要考虑活动的优先顺序，以便我们将大部分时间花在我们真正想做的事情上。

examination_example.sentence: The FSA says it is not telling people to cut <highlight>out</highlight> roast foods entirely, but to reduce their lifetime intake.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国食品标准局表示，这并不是要让人们完全不吃烤肉，而是要减少他们一生中烤肉的摄入量。

examination_example.sentence: They're encouraging you, the consumer, to swap <highlight>out</highlight> your single-use plastic staples like straws and cutlery to combat the plastics crisis.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们正在鼓励你作为消费者去替换类似吸管、餐具等一次性的塑料产品来对抗塑料危机。

sense_info_list.en: situated far or at a particular distance from somewhere

examination_example.sentence: Keep highly polluting cars <highlight>out</highlight> of certain areas—city centres, "school streets", even individual roads.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 让高污染汽车远离某些地区——市中心、学校街道、甚至个别道路。

examination_example.sentence: Ants keep predatory insects away from where their aphids feed; Gmail keeps the spammers <highlight>out</highlight> of our inboxes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 蚂蚁让食肉昆虫远离蚜虫的食物；Gmail让垃圾邮件制造者远离我们的收件箱。

examination_example.sentence: Keeping outsiders <highlight>out</highlight> of a law firm isolates lawyers from the pressure to make money rather than serve clients ethically.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不让外部人士涉足法律事务所业务，可避免律师迫于压力只顾挣钱，而不是按照职业道德服务客户。

sense_info_list.zh: (carry out)实施; 执行; 完成

examination_example.sentence: Carry it <highlight>out</highlight> before the year of 2020.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在2020年之前实施。

examination_example.sentence: The Administration was in essence asserting that because it didn't want to carry <highlight>out</highlight> Congress's immigration wishes, no state should be allowed to do so either.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 政府实际上是在坚称，它不想执行国会的移民管理意愿，所以任何州也不应被允许执行。

examination_example.sentence: Facts about the world are waiting to be collected by objective researchers who use the scientific method to carry <highlight>out</highlight> their work.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 关于这个世界的事实正在等待着被客观的研究人员观察和收集，这些研究人员会使用科学方法执行他们自己工作。

sense_info_list.en: used to show that something or somebody is removed from a place, job, etc.

examination_example.sentence: We converted all the suitable land to fields of fruit and veg, which would involve taking <highlight>out</highlight> all the nature reserves.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们把所有合适的土地都改造成水果和蔬菜田，这将清除所有的自然保护区。

examination_example.sentence: The state's proposed Forest Carbon Plan aims to double efforts to thin <highlight>out</highlight> young trees and clear brush in parts of the forest.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 国家提出的森林碳计划旨在付出加倍努力，减少幼树和清理部分森林的灌木丛。

examination_example.sentence: To filter <highlight>out</highlight> what is unique from what is shared might enable us to understand how complex cultural behavior arose.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 从共同点中过滤掉独特之处，或许能让我们理解复杂的文化行为的产生方式。

sense_info_list.en: to begin your life, or the part of your life when you work, in a particular way

examination_example.sentence: What you start <highlight>out</highlight> trying to achieve may not come to life the way that you expected.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你开始想要呈现的效果最终可能并不会像你期望的那样实现。

examination_example.sentence: In the aftermath of the searing Great Recession, those just starting <highlight>out</highlight> in life are defining priorities and expectations.
